1
00:00:06,006 --> 00:00:08,007
[theme music playing]

2
00:01:03,229 --> 00:01:05,982
GENIE, MAKE A WISH

3
00:01:07,358 --> 00:01:10,403
- So, what are you saying?
- There's something I do want.

4
00:01:10,487 --> 00:01:12,697
I've thought of something
I don't want taken away.

5
00:01:12,781 --> 00:01:13,907
Grandma.

6
00:01:14,657 --> 00:01:15,492
Huh?

7
00:01:16,159 --> 00:01:16,993
Pan-geum?

8
00:01:17,786 --> 00:01:20,455
- I am ready to make my second wish.
- Whoa, wait, wait, wait.

9
00:01:21,122 --> 00:01:23,166
Just think about it carefully.

10
00:01:24,709 --> 00:01:26,795
Think long and hard about this calmly.

11
00:01:27,420 --> 00:01:29,964
Are you really willing
to give up your soul for this?

12
00:01:33,384 --> 00:01:37,889
I want Grandma young.
So make Pan-geum my exact age.

13
00:01:39,390 --> 00:01:42,519
That's it. This will be the second wish.

14
00:01:45,063 --> 00:01:46,898
- [scoffs]
- But not immediately.

15
00:01:46,981 --> 00:01:47,982
Tomorrow's the wake.

16
00:01:50,026 --> 00:01:52,904
Fulfill it in… three days, precisely.

17
00:01:54,948 --> 00:01:56,950
You're scheduling your wish?

18
00:02:01,412 --> 00:02:02,747
- Hawaii?
- [Ka-young] Mm.

19
00:02:03,373 --> 00:02:06,459
Yes, we are going to Hawaii.
Some fresh air. We fly in three days.

20
00:02:06,543 --> 00:02:09,045
- Monday.
- On Monday? But there's so much to do--

21
00:02:09,129 --> 00:02:11,798
It's all been planned.
All you have to do is join me.

22
00:02:12,841 --> 00:02:15,135
I bought the tickets already.
Non-refundable.

23
00:02:15,218 --> 00:02:18,138
Already? Oh, wow. Oh, well, in that case…

24
00:02:18,847 --> 00:02:21,266
In that case,
we can't let these go to waste.

25
00:02:22,308 --> 00:02:24,018
We have to go, of course we do.

26
00:02:24,644 --> 00:02:28,064
My goodness. Ka-young, am I dreaming?

27
00:02:28,148 --> 00:02:30,567
Go brag about it
to the other grandmothers. Okay?

28
00:02:31,192 --> 00:02:32,610
Tell everybody, all right?

29
00:02:33,653 --> 00:02:34,487
All right.

30
00:02:36,239 --> 00:02:38,074
- [Heung-rye] Hawaii?
- Yeah.

31
00:02:38,658 --> 00:02:42,370
I told her it wasn't worth the bother,
but dear Ka-young insisted on a vacation

32
00:02:42,453 --> 00:02:44,998
and booked the flights just like that!
Non-refundable.

33
00:02:45,081 --> 00:02:48,209
- So, I have to go.
- How rich is she?

34
00:02:48,293 --> 00:02:50,211
Working like that on cars?

35
00:02:50,920 --> 00:02:54,132
- I guess she saved everything she could.
- [laughs]

36
00:02:54,215 --> 00:02:57,802
You must be getting your good karma
in one fell swoop. I'm so jealous.

37
00:02:58,428 --> 00:03:00,513
When do you leave?
Take some kimchi with you.

38
00:03:00,597 --> 00:03:02,557
- I've heard the food is heavy.
- On Monday.

39
00:03:02,640 --> 00:03:06,477
Oh, you know, I'm heading
to the market today to get what I need.

40
00:03:06,561 --> 00:03:08,396
Does anyone want me to pick up anything?

41
00:03:08,479 --> 00:03:12,650
She's heading to Seoul tonight. You didn't
forget we're seeing the doctor, did you?

42
00:03:12,734 --> 00:03:16,112
The only trips you book for me
are appointments with that damn doctor.

43
00:03:16,195 --> 00:03:18,740
Why don't you ever
book a flight to Hawaii?

44
00:03:18,823 --> 00:03:22,035
[Da-jin] My goodness. [claps]
All right, everyone, class has begun.

45
00:03:22,118 --> 00:03:24,746
Let's start with a nice, big stretch.

46
00:03:24,829 --> 00:03:25,830
Up!

47
00:03:25,914 --> 00:03:27,206
[Bok-ja groans]

48
00:03:27,290 --> 00:03:29,626
- And to your right.
- Oh, my right.

49
00:03:30,835 --> 00:03:32,170
Oh. Manager Kang.

50
00:03:32,253 --> 00:03:33,504
[line ringing]

51
00:03:33,588 --> 00:03:35,173
Manager Kang, hello.

52
00:03:35,256 --> 00:03:38,426
It appears Ka-young
is taking Pan-geum to Hawaii.

53
00:03:38,968 --> 00:03:41,888
She's had a hard time,
but I'm glad she gets a vacation.

54
00:03:42,472 --> 00:03:45,016
If you want a vacation,
you could see if your son will take you.

55
00:03:47,018 --> 00:03:48,978
[chuckles] Oh, no. I couldn't, no.

56
00:03:49,729 --> 00:03:52,482
- Can't have him splurge on little ol' me.
- [line rings]

57
00:03:52,565 --> 00:03:54,442
- [sighs]
- [line rings]

58
00:03:54,525 --> 00:03:58,488
I'll have your sister-in-law do
the ancestral rites, so don't you worry.

59
00:03:58,571 --> 00:04:00,823
- [line ringing]
- All right.

60
00:04:01,532 --> 00:04:05,745
I won't be able to attend anyway.
I'm supposed to go to Seoul for Jeong-hwa.

61
00:04:06,496 --> 00:04:07,330
What?

62
00:04:07,872 --> 00:04:09,457
Why, is everything all right?

63
00:04:09,540 --> 00:04:11,334
[line rings]

64
00:04:15,046 --> 00:04:16,506
[Im-seon] Where the hell are you?

65
00:04:16,589 --> 00:04:18,925
[Jeong-hwa] <i>I'm at the prep academy.</i>
<i>Where else would I be?</i>

66
00:04:19,008 --> 00:04:22,762
Well, I'm at your place right now.
You thought I'd never swing by here?

67
00:04:23,346 --> 00:04:25,139
- Ugh.
<i>- I swear, I am ending your lease!</i>

68
00:04:25,223 --> 00:04:27,433
Is this why you never wanted me here?

69
00:04:29,018 --> 00:04:31,771
[shouts] Do you know what the hell
I just found in your trash?

70
00:04:31,854 --> 00:04:34,816
You're pissing me off! Who gave you
permission to snoop through my stuff?

71
00:04:34,899 --> 00:04:36,442
[scoffs] Permission?

72
00:04:36,526 --> 00:04:38,278
Do you even go to class?

73
00:04:38,361 --> 00:04:40,863
<i>Right. Well,</i>
<i>I was gonna tell you anyway.</i>

74
00:04:40,947 --> 00:04:44,117
<i>I want to stop prepping for the college</i>
<i>exam. I'm not gonna go to college.</i>

75
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:46,202
Oh, you're just not going?

76
00:04:46,995 --> 00:04:50,248
[scoffs] Tell me how you're gonna
make it in life without college?

77
00:04:50,915 --> 00:04:52,041
Tell me how.

78
00:04:52,125 --> 00:04:54,085
Tell me how you'll manage,
help me understand!

79
00:04:54,168 --> 00:04:56,087
I can still have a good life
without school!

80
00:04:56,671 --> 00:04:59,757
Do you even know the privileges you enjoy?

81
00:04:59,841 --> 00:05:01,259
<i>- I'm hanging up!</i>
<i>- </i>[line disconnects]

82
00:05:01,342 --> 00:05:02,343
Hello?

83
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:05,013
Yoo Jeong-hwa!

84
00:05:05,972 --> 00:05:07,849
- God! How could she!
- [cell phone clatters]

85
00:05:07,932 --> 00:05:11,352
Seriously. [sobbing]

86
00:05:21,279 --> 00:05:23,656
God, back when I was just a cashier…

87
00:05:24,657 --> 00:05:27,869
[sniffles] we practically never fought.

88
00:05:30,288 --> 00:05:32,040
Oh, my little girl.

89
00:05:32,123 --> 00:05:34,000
[Iblis] You can always go back, you know?

90
00:05:34,083 --> 00:05:36,627
[Im-seon sobbing]

91
00:05:36,711 --> 00:05:38,421
You have one wish remaining.

92
00:05:39,630 --> 00:05:40,923
You could undo it all.

93
00:05:45,178 --> 00:05:46,179
[sniffles]

94
00:05:46,262 --> 00:05:48,514
[ominous music playing]

95
00:05:48,598 --> 00:05:49,599
[breath shudders]

96
00:05:51,100 --> 00:05:52,935
I can't just waste it on that.

97
00:05:54,771 --> 00:05:56,439
It's too valuable.

98
00:05:59,609 --> 00:06:00,485
It is.

99
00:06:02,028 --> 00:06:03,029
[chuckles quietly]

100
00:06:03,905 --> 00:06:07,992
- [watch ticking]
- 1,044, 1,045,

101
00:06:08,076 --> 00:06:11,245
1,046, 1,047.

102
00:06:16,793 --> 00:06:18,294
What the… Where is he?

103
00:06:20,129 --> 00:06:21,130
Where is he?

104
00:06:21,714 --> 00:06:23,174
[whooshing]

105
00:06:24,926 --> 00:06:27,553
[groaning]

106
00:06:27,637 --> 00:06:30,014
Hey, where have you been?
Why weren't you on time?

107
00:06:30,098 --> 00:06:32,433
Deadline's in 15 seconds.
My wish fulfilled?

108
00:06:32,517 --> 00:06:33,434
[scoffs]

109
00:06:35,019 --> 00:06:35,853
Are you blind?

110
00:06:37,105 --> 00:06:39,065
We still have three seconds to go.

111
00:06:39,148 --> 00:06:42,235
[watch ticking thrice]

112
00:06:43,111 --> 00:06:44,445
[alarm chimes]

113
00:06:45,196 --> 00:06:46,280
[energy chimes]

114
00:06:48,366 --> 00:06:50,451
[suspenseful music playing]

115
00:06:50,535 --> 00:06:53,663
[Iblis] <i>Your second wish</i>
<i>has now been fulfilled.</i>

116
00:07:01,420 --> 00:07:03,673
- Grandma, you asleep?
- [cell phone clatters]

117
00:07:05,258 --> 00:07:09,095
Oh, dear. What time is it?
Is it already time to go to the airport?

118
00:07:09,679 --> 00:07:13,015
Oh, my goodness.
I haven't even finished packing yet.

119
00:07:14,350 --> 00:07:15,226
[groans]

120
00:07:15,768 --> 00:07:18,312
What in the world?
How did this come loose?

121
00:07:20,148 --> 00:07:21,149
[sighs]

122
00:07:22,442 --> 00:07:24,569
We should take kimchi
and gochujang, right?

123
00:07:24,652 --> 00:07:26,654
[music intensifies]

124
00:07:30,950 --> 00:07:31,868
Grandma.

125
00:07:33,244 --> 00:07:35,746
- You were pretty.
- What are you saying?

126
00:07:36,330 --> 00:07:38,833
I'm swollen,
I fell asleep right after dinner.

127
00:07:39,667 --> 00:07:41,085
[clears throat]

128
00:07:41,794 --> 00:07:42,920
Why is my voice…

129
00:07:43,004 --> 00:07:45,590
You are so much prettier
than I ever imagined.

130
00:07:45,673 --> 00:07:48,134
I just woke up. What is this?

131
00:07:48,217 --> 00:07:51,512
Where do you think your face came from?
It all started here. [chuckles]

132
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:55,266
Ah, yeah, let's see, let's see.

133
00:07:55,850 --> 00:07:59,061
We should at least have a few boiled eggs
before we go, right?

134
00:08:00,146 --> 00:08:02,398
[yelps, gasps] Oh, she startled me.

135
00:08:03,191 --> 00:08:04,942
Who's this? This a friend of yours?

136
00:08:05,026 --> 00:08:07,445
No. You know I have
no other friends than Min-ji.

137
00:08:08,196 --> 00:08:09,155
Then who is that?

138
00:08:12,325 --> 00:08:14,577
I've seen that face before.

139
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:17,705
She's so familiar.

140
00:08:17,788 --> 00:08:19,790
[suspenseful music plays]

141
00:08:21,626 --> 00:08:23,002
My God.

142
00:08:23,878 --> 00:08:25,755
[gasps] Am I…

143
00:08:26,881 --> 00:08:29,217
- Is this a dream or what?
- You could say that.

144
00:08:29,926 --> 00:08:31,135
Do you know who that is?

145
00:08:33,054 --> 00:08:34,972
[breath trembling]

146
00:08:36,557 --> 00:08:38,601
[gasping]

147
00:08:40,811 --> 00:08:42,230
I know this face.

148
00:08:43,731 --> 00:08:46,984
This… This beautiful young face
belongs to…

149
00:08:47,068 --> 00:08:49,445
[gasping]

150
00:08:49,529 --> 00:08:53,157
Uh, if you faint, do it to your left.

151
00:08:54,116 --> 00:08:54,951
[groans]

152
00:08:58,246 --> 00:08:59,163
[gasps]

153
00:09:00,206 --> 00:09:03,751
The young lady who had her pick
of every eligible boy.

154
00:09:03,834 --> 00:09:05,294
[gasps, groans]

155
00:09:07,171 --> 00:09:09,966
I can wear a fancy outfit
from my grandbaby's closet!

156
00:09:10,508 --> 00:09:13,219
Even squeeze into
a pair of pointy heels! [sighs]

157
00:09:14,262 --> 00:09:18,474
[gasping] Oh, goodness! Lord Buddha!

158
00:09:18,558 --> 00:09:23,271
Gods above and below!
Virgin Mary! Thank you!

159
00:09:23,354 --> 00:09:24,772
- [groans]
- [body thuds]

160
00:09:26,691 --> 00:09:28,568
It wasn't any of them.

161
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:31,696
- It was someone from the Middle East.
- [scoffs smugly]

162
00:09:32,405 --> 00:09:33,823
[dramatic music plays]

163
00:09:33,906 --> 00:09:37,076
I know what this is. It's that notebook.
Your writing.

164
00:09:37,159 --> 00:09:38,869
- Wishes!
- Yeah.

165
00:09:38,953 --> 00:09:41,330
So, it's real? It won't undo overnight?

166
00:09:44,208 --> 00:09:45,167
[chuckles excitedly]

167
00:09:45,251 --> 00:09:47,169
Uh… [sighs]

168
00:09:48,671 --> 00:09:49,839
[gasps]

169
00:09:51,882 --> 00:09:53,593
Grandma? What are you doing?

170
00:09:54,343 --> 00:09:57,138
Which one's the Chanel? [gasping]

171
00:09:57,221 --> 00:09:59,432
[hangers clacking]

172
00:09:59,515 --> 00:10:01,434
[birds cawing]

173
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:08,274
Really?

174
00:10:09,317 --> 00:10:12,028
I'm surprised so much occurred
in such a small town.

175
00:10:15,489 --> 00:10:16,407
[grunts]

176
00:10:18,951 --> 00:10:19,869
[Ejllael exhales]

177
00:10:19,952 --> 00:10:23,414
Am I mistaken or have you
been exercising more lately?

178
00:10:23,497 --> 00:10:26,208
I might be deploying my wings more
in the coming days. [pants]

179
00:10:28,044 --> 00:10:29,378
My clothes keep tearing.

180
00:10:29,462 --> 00:10:31,631
So, you're just not gonna wear anything?

181
00:10:31,714 --> 00:10:35,009
Manufacturing one piece of clothing
uses 7,000 liters of water.

182
00:10:35,092 --> 00:10:37,511
So you plan to just fly naked.

183
00:10:37,595 --> 00:10:40,222
[sighs] Focus. Anything to report?

184
00:10:41,307 --> 00:10:43,392
Ms. Ki Ka-young has made another wish.

185
00:10:43,476 --> 00:10:46,395
And it is indeed a noble one.
Congratulations.

186
00:10:47,021 --> 00:10:49,690
You know a noble wish
doesn't guarantee noble results.

187
00:10:50,441 --> 00:10:51,692
We need to stay vigilant.

188
00:10:53,527 --> 00:10:54,779
And Iblis, where is he?

189
00:10:55,863 --> 00:10:58,324
[Iblis] So what?
She made her grandma young.

190
00:10:58,407 --> 00:11:01,160
What about it?
That count as righteous? [scoffs]

191
00:11:01,827 --> 00:11:03,204
[sighs nervously]

192
00:11:04,288 --> 00:11:07,375
Whatever. Don't get obsessed
by such minor details.

193
00:11:07,458 --> 00:11:10,002
That market employee,
her first wish was wicked.

194
00:11:11,629 --> 00:11:13,714
Yeah. You're doing great.

195
00:11:15,675 --> 00:11:17,802
But why do you insist
on sitting like this?

196
00:11:17,885 --> 00:11:18,969
[groans] My back.

197
00:11:20,763 --> 00:11:23,516
[groaning]

198
00:11:29,021 --> 00:11:30,856
[tense music plays]

199
00:11:30,940 --> 00:11:33,859
When did I give you permission
to just waltz in here?

200
00:11:33,943 --> 00:11:36,529
Did I give you permission
to show up at my building?

201
00:11:38,656 --> 00:11:41,367
So Irem chirped away again. Hey.

202
00:11:41,951 --> 00:11:45,496
I imagine you're all excited about
Ki Ka-young making a righteous wish.

203
00:11:45,579 --> 00:11:48,290
But her first wish was still enough
for me to slit her throat.

204
00:11:48,374 --> 00:11:49,708
[scoffs] Blah, blah, blah.

205
00:11:49,792 --> 00:11:52,294
So, being that was born on Wednesday,
would you kindly let me

206
00:11:52,378 --> 00:11:54,713
continue my internal contemplations
and get the hell out?

207
00:11:54,797 --> 00:11:57,049
[laughs] Contemplations?

208
00:11:57,133 --> 00:12:00,302
Looked like panic to me, wouldn't you say,
Satan, born on Thursday?

209
00:12:00,386 --> 00:12:03,848
Huh? You think I… [laughing]

210
00:12:03,931 --> 00:12:07,226
Oh, if you were to analyze the faces
of the other two wishers,

211
00:12:07,309 --> 00:12:10,646
oh, it's so amazing.
They're all but guaranteed to be damned.

212
00:12:10,729 --> 00:12:14,817
Oh, and the dog?
Ooh, yeah, it's in the bag. Sorry, bro.

213
00:12:14,900 --> 00:12:17,111
Didn't I warn you
to stop disrupting the human world?

214
00:12:17,194 --> 00:12:19,155
A dog turns into a man
and you think that's that?

215
00:12:19,238 --> 00:12:21,449
- Meh, meh, meh, meh…
- An old lady becomes young again.

216
00:12:21,532 --> 00:12:24,577
What about everyone's memories, huh?
Giving them gold? How's that gonna work?

217
00:12:24,660 --> 00:12:28,122
You can't walk into a bank with massive
bags of gold without getting flagged!

218
00:12:28,205 --> 00:12:29,874
Your methods? They're really outdated.

219
00:12:30,458 --> 00:12:33,002
Face it.
You no longer have a purpose here.

220
00:12:33,085 --> 00:12:35,921
Well, even so, that's mean.

221
00:12:37,715 --> 00:12:38,841
You're just gassing.

222
00:12:39,341 --> 00:12:40,509
"Gaslighting."

223
00:12:40,593 --> 00:12:41,427
Oh.

224
00:12:42,636 --> 00:12:43,679
Sade, you idiot!

225
00:12:45,473 --> 00:12:48,267
And what if I can prove to you
I've got value?

226
00:12:48,851 --> 00:12:51,187
- [sighs]
- [man] Genie! Genie!

227
00:12:52,188 --> 00:12:54,607
Where are you? Mr. Genie, sir?

228
00:12:54,690 --> 00:12:56,066
Do your best to prove it, then.

229
00:12:57,151 --> 00:12:58,903
Everyone's gonna want you now.

230
00:12:59,778 --> 00:13:01,697
You better not disturb me
in my lamp again.

231
00:13:02,990 --> 00:13:04,783
Okay, I'm coming, dog!

232
00:13:04,867 --> 00:13:06,035
Where are you?

233
00:13:06,118 --> 00:13:07,578
[whooshing]

234
00:13:10,664 --> 00:13:14,084
Can you help me? I only know dog things.
[breathing shakily]

235
00:13:14,835 --> 00:13:18,631
I look like a human, you know?
But what can I do?

236
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:22,009
Nothing. I'm hopeless.

237
00:13:22,593 --> 00:13:23,511
Help me.

238
00:13:23,594 --> 00:13:27,056
So, your second wish
is the same as your first wish?

239
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:29,391
What's with the speech? [laughs]

240
00:13:29,475 --> 00:13:30,351
Is it a shtick?

241
00:13:30,434 --> 00:13:32,061
No, no. No, no, no, no, no.

242
00:13:32,144 --> 00:13:34,939
No, no, my father was
a show dog. High class.

243
00:13:35,648 --> 00:13:39,193
But I can't do anything
without, uh, money, uh, picture ID.

244
00:13:39,902 --> 00:13:42,738
- Money. A picture ID. I need them.
